post_text:
The Illinois State Board of Education is excited to share today's announcement from the USDA that they are extending waivers for Summer Meals programs through the end of this calendar year. This will allow schools participating in the Child Nutrition Programs to continue serving free reimbursable meals to all children through Dec. 31, 2020.

As of Sept.1st breakfast and lunch for all Knoxville students are now free through Dec. 2020. You must still preorder meals on EVERY e-learning day by 8 a.m. and place an order for each child. Younger siblings not in school are now included. The order form can be found at Bluebullets.org under the Food Service tab. There is also a menu posted for pick up meals under the tab as well. We will continue to deliver to the sites listed on the form for easier access for everyone.

post_text: Knoxville schools will be serving grab and go lunches and breakfasts free of charge to all students during the mandatory closure. Distribution will begin tomorrow, Tuesday, March 17, and continue on weekdays through Monday, March 30. Meals can be picked up at Knoxville High School from 11:30 a.m. to 12:30 p.m. daily. More information about meal distribution can be found on the district website under the News tab.
